P = (X:Y:Z:T) in completed coordinates (i.e., with affine coordinates given via X/Z = x and Y/T = y),
it computes an equivalent representation (X':Y':Z':T') in extended coordinates
(i.e., with X'/Z' = x, Y'/Z' = y and T' = X'Y'/Z')

